@startuml
title The Intelligent Bike - Deployment Sequence Diagram

actor Developer
participant "Local Dev\nEnvironment" as DevEnv
participant "Git Repository" as Git
participant "Heroku Platform" as Heroku
participant "Heroku Buildpack" as Buildpack
participant "PostgreSQL\nDatabase" as PostgresDB
participant "MQTT Broker" as MQTT
participant "Django Backend\n(WSGI)" as Django
participant "Node.js Server\n(Angular)" as NodeServer
participant "Hardware\n(Raspberry Pi)" as Hardware

== Development Phase ==
Developer -> DevEnv: Develop backend\n(Django + SQLite)
activate DevEnv
DevEnv -> DevEnv: Run manage.py\nmigrate
DevEnv -> DevEnv: Test with SQLite
deactivate DevEnv

Developer -> DevEnv: Develop frontend\n(Angular)
activate DevEnv
DevEnv -> DevEnv: ng serve
DevEnv -> DevEnv: Test locally
deactivate DevEnv

Developer -> DevEnv: Develop hardware\nscripts (Python)
activate DevEnv
DevEnv -> DevEnv: Test MQTT\npublish/subscribe
deactivate DevEnv

== Backend Deployment ==
Developer -> Git: Push backend code
activate Git
Git -> Heroku: Trigger deployment
deactivate Git

activate Heroku
Heroku -> Buildpack: Detect Python app
activate Buildpack
Buildpack -> Buildpack: Read requirements.txt
Buildpack -> Buildpack: Install dependencies\n(Django, DRF, MQTT)
Buildpack --> Heroku: Build complete
deactivate Buildpack

Heroku -> Heroku: Read Procfile
Heroku -> PostgresDB: Provision PostgreSQL\naddon
activate PostgresDB
PostgresDB --> Heroku: Database credentials
deactivate PostgresDB

Heroku -> Django: Run migrations
activate Django
Django -> PostgresDB: CREATE TABLE sensors
activate PostgresDB
PostgresDB --> Django: Tables created
deactivate PostgresDB

Heroku -> Django: Start WSGI server\n(gunicorn)
Django -> Django: Load settings.py
Django -> PostgresDB: Connect to database
activate PostgresDB
PostgresDB --> Django: Connection established
deactivate PostgresDB

Django -> MQTT: Subscribe to topics
activate MQTT
MQTT --> Django: Subscription confirmed
Django --> Heroku: Backend running
deactivate Django
deactivate Heroku

== Frontend Deployment ==
Developer -> Git: Push frontend code
activate Git
Git -> Heroku: Trigger deployment
deactivate Git

activate Heroku
Heroku -> Buildpack: Detect Node.js app
activate Buildpack
Buildpack -> Buildpack: Read package.json
Buildpack -> Buildpack: npm install
Buildpack -> Buildpack: ng build --prod
Buildpack --> Heroku: Build complete
deactivate Buildpack

Heroku -> Heroku: Read Procfile
Heroku -> NodeServer: Start Node.js server
activate NodeServer
NodeServer -> NodeServer: Load server.js
NodeServer -> NodeServer: Serve static files
NodeServer --> Heroku: Frontend running
deactivate NodeServer
deactivate Heroku

== Hardware Deployment ==
Developer -> Hardware: Deploy Python scripts
activate Hardware
Hardware -> Hardware: Install dependencies\n(DHT22, GPIO libs)
Hardware -> Hardware: Configure sensors
Hardware -> MQTT: Connect to broker
MQTT --> Hardware: Connection established
Hardware -> Hardware: Start main.py
Hardware --> Developer: Hardware deployed
deactivate Hardware

== Runtime Verification ==
Developer -> NodeServer: Access dashboard URL
activate NodeServer
NodeServer --> Developer: Serve Angular app
deactivate NodeServer

Developer -> Django: Test API endpoints
activate Django
Django -> PostgresDB: Query sensor data
activate PostgresDB
PostgresDB --> Django: Return data
deactivate PostgresDB
Django --> Developer: JSON response
deactivate Django

Hardware -> Hardware: Read sensors
activate Hardware
Hardware -> MQTT: Publish sensor data
deactivate Hardware

activate MQTT
MQTT -> Django: Forward message
deactivate MQTT

activate Django
Django -> PostgresDB: INSERT sensor values
activate PostgresDB
PostgresDB --> Django: Data stored
deactivate PostgresDB
deactivate Django

Developer -> NodeServer: Refresh dashboard
activate NodeServer
NodeServer -> Django: GET /api/sensors
activate Django
Django -> PostgresDB: SELECT sensor values
activate PostgresDB
PostgresDB --> Django: Latest data
deactivate PostgresDB
Django --> NodeServer: JSON response
deactivate Django
NodeServer --> Developer: Display sensor data
deactivate NodeServer

@enduml
